<div>		



<span class="section_title">2005 INTERNATIONAL CES Rolls Out The Red Carpet For Celebrities</span>

<br><br>		
<strong><i>Arlington, Virginia&nbsp;-&nbsp;1/3/2005</i></strong>
<br><br>
From actors and athletes to musicians and comedians, the 2005 International CES plays host to some of the top entertainment and sports celebrities in the world.   Celebrity guests will mingle with the latest and greatest consumer products and technologies at CES, the world’s largest annual technology tradeshow, January 6-9 in Las Vegas, Nevada.  
<p>      
Several International CES exhibitors plan to house major entertainment in their booths. Rock and roll fans will not want to miss three days of live concerts from Olympus Imaging America.  Catch the Black Crowes' Chris and Rich Robinson on Thursday, January 6, Cheap Trick on Friday, January 7, and Randy Jackson of Zebra on Saturday, January 8.  All performances will take place at the Olympus booth, Central Hall #14427, at 3:00 p.m.
<p>
XM Satellite Radio will feature appearances and live performances by a number of notable personalities, including: hip-hop artist Ludacris; baseball legend Cal Ripken, Jr.; award-winning journalist and XM Public Radio host Bob Edwards; Playboy Radio hosts Juli and Tiffany; REO Speedwagon's Kevin Cronin and Dave Amato; XM talk radio personalities Opie & Anthony; jazz icon Al Jarreau; Darryl "D.M.C." McDaniels of the legendary rap group Run D.M.C., and others.  Times and dates will be announced on-site, but all the action will take place at XM's booth, North Hall #4606.
<p>      
Continuing the satellite radio trend, Sirius Satellite Radio also will present a full schedule of entertainment programming and autograph sessions throughout the show.  Check out the following line-up at the Sirius Stage in the Central Hall, booth #9817:
<p>      
Thursday, January 6<br>
11:00-12:00 p.m.<br>
Maxim Radio with Even Roberts and Brian O’Leary, guests Maxim <br>		
January Calendar Girl Joanna Krupa and models Marta Krupa and Rebecca Newell<br>
2:00-3:30 p.m.<br>
Autograph session with Joanna and Marta Krupa<br>
2:30-3:30 p.m.<br>
Jim Breuer "Unleashed"<br>
3:30-4:30 p.m.<br>
Autograph session with Jim Breuer<br>
4:00-5:00 p.m.<br>
One More Saturday Night with Bill Walton with guest Grateful Dead Drummer, Bill Kreutzmann<br>
5:00-5:30 p.m.<br>
Autograph session with Bill Walton and Bill Kreutzmann<br>
<p>
Friday, January 7<br>
10:00-12:00 p.m.<br>
The Red Zone with Chris Carter and Steve Cohen, guest Tony Gonzalez<br>
12:00-4:00 p.m.<br>
The Afternoon Blitz with John Riggins and Adam Schein, guest Keyshawn Johnson<br>
4:00-6:00 p.m.<br>
Autograph session with the Dallas Cowboy Cheerleaders<br>
<p>
Saturday, January 8<br>
9:00-10:00 a.m.<br>
Elvis Radio - The Las Vegas Connection with Mojo Nixon, guests Dick Grob, Ed Bonja, Cynthia Pepper and Cathy Spehar<br>
10:30-12:30 p.m.<br>
BIG 80s VJs in Las Vegas with Mark Goodman, Nina Blackwood and Alan Hunter, guests Jane Wiedlin and John Waite<br>
12:30-1:00 p.m.<br>
Autograph session with BIG 80s VJs<br>
1:00-2:00 p.m.<br>
Tony Hawk's Demolition Radio, guest Tom Green<br>
2:30-3:30 p.m.<br>
The Wiseguy Show, guests Robert Goulet, Ed McMahon, Wayne Newton and Lance Burton<br>
5:30-6:00 p.m.<br>
Autograph session with The Wiseguys<br>
<p>      
For the music lover at CES, meet and greet the names behind the hits at the Studio@Home pavilion in the CES South Plaza.  Six Grammy-winning producers will be telling behind-the-music studio tales and demonstrating 5.1 surround sound demos:
<p>
Thursday, January 6<br>
12:00 p.m.	Elliot Schneiner (The Eagles, Steely Dan and Beck)<br>
<p>
Friday, January 7<br>
3:00 p.m.	Al Schmitt (Diana Krall and Frank Sinatra)<br>
4:00 p.m.	Frank Fililpetti (James Taylor and Korn)<br>
5:00 p.m.	Rory Kaplan (Queen)<br>
<p>
Saturday, January 8<br>
4:30 p.m.	Ed Cherney (Bonnie Raitt and the Rolling Stones)<br>
5:30 p.m.	George Massenburg (Linda Ronstadt and Earth, Wind & Fire)<br>
<p>      
In addition, a number of exhibitors plan to hold invitation-only events featuring major music superstars at CES.  On Friday, January 7, Rod Stewart will headline Monster’s annual Dealer Awards and Samsung will host an exclusive dinner with Bon Jovi.  On Saturday, January 8, Gibson Guitar will throw its own bash honoring guitar legend Les Paul with guest star Ike Turner.
<p>       
Other noteworthy celebrities will be on the show floor in full force promoting products and signing autographs, including: 
<p>      
2004 Indianapolis 500 Champion Buddy Rice and 2005 JRL driver Danica Patrick - Pioneer will host an autograph session with these two racing stars on Friday, January 7, from 10:00-12:00 p.m., in their booth, Central Hall #9826.
<p>      
Hall of Fame Quarterback Jim Kelly - Polaroid will feature an autograph and interview session with the Buffalo Bills legend on Friday, January 7, from 2:00-5:00 p.m., in their booth, Central Hall #14400.
<p>      
Jackie Chan and Tom Arnold - SSD Company/Xavix will bring these two superstars to Las Vegas for an autograph singing on Thursday, January 6, and Friday, January 7, in their booth, South Hall #31744.  Jackie Chan also will be a special guest at SSD/Xavix press event on Thursday, January 6, at 11:00 a.m.
<p>      
NASCAR driver Kyle Busch - Delphi will continue its partnership with Hendrick Motorsports and will be an associate sponsor of the Kellog No. 5 Chevrolet in the NASCAR Nextel Cup series.  They will introduce Busch, the No. 5 car driver, at their press conference on January 5, from 1:00-1:30 p.m. in booth #5206 in the North Hall.
<p>      
West Coast Customs Crew from MTV's "Pimp My Ride" - Ryan, Mad Mike, Alex and 2Shae will appear at the Directed Electronics press conference and booth in the North Hall, booth #301.  Get a peek at Directed's newest products in off-the-hook West Coast Customs' vehicles.
<p>      
The 2004 International CES focuses on more than 30 product areas from more than 2,400 exhibitors spread throughout more than 1.5 million net square feet of space at the Las Vegas Convention Center, the Las Vegas Hilton and the Alexis Park Resort.  For changes and updates to the celebrity list at CES, be sure to visit http://www.CESweb.org/attendees/special_events/celebs.asp.
<p>
Note to Journalists:  	Journalists are encouraged to arrive in Las Vegas by Tuesday, January 4, 2005 to take advantage of all the CES press conferences and events.  CES Unveiled: The Official Press Event of the International CES will run January 4 from 4:00 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. in the Las Vegas Convention Center, room S226, across the hallway from the CES Press Room.  A list of press room hours and services is posted at www.CESweb.org, the interactive source for CES information.
<p>      
About CEA:<br>
The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) is the preeminent trade association promoting growth in the consumer technology industry through technology policy, events, research, promotion and the fostering of business and strategic relationships.  CEA represents more than 1,800 corporate members involved in the design, development, manufacturing, distribution and integration of audio, video, mobile electronics, wireless and landline communications, information technology, home networking, multimedia and accessory products, as well as related services that are sold through consumer channels. Combined, CEA's members account for more than $110 billion in annual sales.  CEA's resources are available online at www.CE.org, the definitive source for information about the consumer electronics industry.<br>
CEA also sponsors and manages the International CES - Defining Tomorrow's Technology.  All profits from CES are reinvested into industry services, including technical training and education, industry promotion, engineering standards development, market research and legislative advocacy.

